Pan-frying gnocchi brings a whole extra dimension to these pillowy little dumplings. The golden, crispy exterior provides a beautiful contrast with today's creamy mushroom sauce. As an added bonus it's incredibly easy to make, leaving you plenty of time to put your feet up. Enjoy!

Put a #large saucepan{} of water on to boil for the broccoli. Halve, peel and finely chop the @echalion shallot{1}(halved, peeled and finely chopped). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated). Cut each @chestnut mushrooms{1}(cut into 4 or 5 slices) into 4 or 5 slices. Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2}(finely chopped).

Put a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} over high heat. Add the mushrooms in small batches and cook until they are golden brown, ~{5%minutes}. Reduce the heat to medium-low and add the shallot. Cook for ~{3-4%minutes}. Then add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. If the pan gets too dry, add a splash of water.

Add the @vegetable stock pot{1/2} and @water{100%ml} to the frying pan. Season with a few good grinds of @black pepper{}. Stir to dissolve the stock pot and simmer over medium heat until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Put a splash of oil in another frying pan on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @gnocchi{300%g}. Gently fry until crispy around the edges, ~{8%minutes}. Remove from the heat. Meanwhile, cut the @broccoli{1} into small florets. Add them to the pan of boiling water. Cook for ~{3-4%minutes}. Then drain in a #colander{} and set aside.

Stir the @creme fraiche{1} into your mushroom sauce. Once heated through, add the gnocchi, broccoli and half the parsley. Give it a good stir, then taste for seasoning and add @salt{} and black pepper as you wish.

Divide your mushroom and broccoli gnocchi between bowls. Top with the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and a sprinkling of the remaining parsley. Buon appetito!